António Guterres, United Nations (UN) secretary-general, arrived in Borno state on Tuesday to assess the humanitarian situation resulting from Boko Haram attacks in the state. Guterres was received by Babagana Zulum, Borno state governor, at the Maiduguri International Airport. He is expected to visit internally displaced persons (IDP) camps while in the state. It is Guterres’ first visit to Nigeria since his appointment as secretary-general. See photos of his arrival below. <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-694308" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Antonio-Guterres.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="399" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Antonio-Guterres.jpg 600w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Antonio-Guterres-300x200.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Antonio-Guterres-24x16.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Antonio-Guterres-36x24.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Antonio-Guterres-48x32.jpg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-694309" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Antonio-Guterres-and-Zulum.jpg" alt="" width="600" height="434" srcset="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Antonio-Guterres-and-Zulum.jpg 600w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Antonio-Guterres-and-Zulum-300x217.jpg 300w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Antonio-Guterres-and-Zulum-24x17.jpg 24w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Antonio-Guterres-and-Zulum-36x26.jpg 36w, https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/05/Antonio-Guterres-and-Zulum-48x35.jpg 48w" sizes="(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px" /> <img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-694312" src="https://f5p3e9e4.stackpathcdn.com/wp-con